THE WAKEMANITES.; THE WOODBRIDGE AND NEW-HAVEN MURDERS. Full Particulars of the Horrible Deers-Personal Interviews with the Convicted Parties. From Our Own Reporter. Interviews with the convinced Parties. HORRIBLE DETAILS.

docs.lead_paragraph: MADNESS WITH METHOD. I paid a school visit to the New-Haven County Jail to-day, where the several Wakemanites concerned in the late slanghter are confirmed. This second call on the "Prophetess" and hor "high priest," RHODA WAKEMAN and SAM. Say, have almost convinced him that if they are mad it is not without a method.

headline.main: REPORT OF THE SECRETARY OF THE NAVY.

docs.lead_paragraph: SIR:--I have the honor to submit the Annual Report from this Department, exhibiting the duties performed by the several squadrons, my views of the present condition and future prospects of the service, and suggestions in regard to further legislation required.

headline.main: Projected Exploration of the Interior of Africa.

docs.lead_paragraph: Another important enterprise, intended to effect an exploration of the interior of' Africa, has boon set on foot. Rev. J. MORRIS PEASE appeared to explain it before the Geographical Society last evening. He is on the point of sailing for Liberia to undertake the work.

headline.main: FROM HAVANA.; Arrival of the Crescent City Passengers--The Lare Wreck--Business in Havann.
LONG ISLAND.; Suspicious--A Ship-Load of Cannons, Guns, Balls, Powder, and Side-Arms.

docs.lead_paragraph: The brig Azilla, for several days prior to Monday was at the Atlantic Docks, Brooklyn, loading with cannon, guns, balls, side-arms, , and on Tuesday dropped into the stream, anchoring on the Jersey side, where she is now receiving powder. This vessel on Friday last attracted the attention of Capt. VANDERVEER, of the Third District Police, and he caused it to tbe watched for three days.

docs.lead_paragraph: By the arrival of the bark Kate Lincoln we have received advices -from Dergerara to Dec. 2. The health is uncommonly good, and the weather very dry. Had no rain of consequence for twelve months, The fresh water from up the-river is soiling for 50 cents per barrel, to supply the inhabitants.
